articles.description: Tennessee is not resting upon its regular-season SEC co-championship with Auburn.
articles.headline: Mississippi State gets rematch with No. 13 Tennessee

articles.description: Chimezie Metu had 22 points and 11 rebounds, and Southern California smothered Oregon State defensively to beat the Beavers 61-48 in the Pac-12 Tournament quarterfinals on Thursday night.
articles.headline: USC knocks off Oregon State 61-48 in Pac-12 quarterfinals

images.caption: Jordan McLaughlin puts the pass on the mark to Chimezie Metu for an alley-oop dunk.
images.name: USC's Metu gets up for alley-oop

articles.description: The star freshman's game-winning shot saved the Crimson Tide's hopes for a bid. Other bubble hopefuls, such as Notre Dame, Marquette and Texas, are feeling less hopeful after losses on Thursday.
articles.headline: Bubble Watch: Collin Sexton to the rescue as Alabama stays alive

images.caption: Collin Sexton's game-winning shot kept Alabama's tourney hopes alive.
images.name: Collin Sexton [576x324]

images.caption: Collin Sexton goes coast-to-coast and hits the game-winning runner to beat the buzzer over Texas A&M.
images.name: Sexton calls game on Texas A&M

articles.description: There might not be a more confident team than the Nevada Wolf Pack.
articles.headline: No. 22 Nevada seeks revenge vs. San Diego State

articles.description: Ivan Canete scored 17 points, TJ Holy field added 16, and Stephen F. Austin ran away from Central Arkansas in the second half to win 86-64 in Thursday night's Southland Conference Tournament quarterfinal.
articles.headline: Stephen F Austin heads to Southland semis

articles.description: Femi Olujobi scored 18 points and grabbed nine rebounds and North Carolina A&T secured its first Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference Tournament semifinal appearance in five years, holding off Norfolk State 70-64 in a quarterfinal battle Thursday night.
articles.headline: North Carolina A&T beats Norfolk St., 70-64; faces Hampton
